<title>USA: Colgate-Palmolive Q4 shr $1.20 vs $0.80.</title>
<headline>Colgate-Palmolive Q4 shr $1.20 vs $0.80.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-02-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Colgate-Palmolive Co Summary of Consolidated Results</p>
<p>Three Months and Years Ended December 31, 1996 and 1995</p>
<p>		  (Dollars in Millions Except Per Share Amounts)</p>
<p>				  Fourth Quarter	     Year</p>
<p>				  1996	  1995	1996     1995</p>
<p> Net Sales		 $2,297.4   $2,152.8  $8,749.0 $8,358.2</p>
<p>Provision for</p>
<p> Restructuring		  ---	  ---	 ---    460.5</p>
<p>Earnings Before</p>
<p> Interest and Taxes	 306.3	240.3   1,152.0    568.9</p>
<p> Net Interest Expense	46.8	 59.6     197.4    205.4</p>
<p>Income Before</p>
<p> Income Taxes		 259.5	180.7     954.6    363.5</p>
<p>Provision for</p>
<p> Income Taxes		  77.8	 58.2     319.6    191.5</p>
<p> Net Income		   181.7	122.5     635.0    172.0</p>
<p>Preferred Dividends,</p>
<p> Net of Tax		     5.3	  5.4	21.4     21.6</p>
<p>Earnings Per Common Share</p>
<p>				   1.20	 0.80	4.19     1.04</p>
<p>Average Common Shares  </p>
<p>Outstanding (in millions)</p>
<p>				  147.1	145.7     146.6    145.2</p>
<p>NOTE: Full year 1995 results include restructuring provision of $369.2 million or $2.54 per share after tax. Excluding this charge, 1995 net was $541.2 million, or $3.58 per share.</p>
<p>Assuming full dilution, earnings per common share were $1.12 vs $0.76 in the fourth quarter and $3.90 vs $1.02 in the full year.</p>
<p>Average common shares used in fully diluted computation were 161,634,000 vs 159,878,000 for the fourth quarter, and 161,287,000 vs 147,769,000 for the full year.  </p>
<p>First Call estimate for 1996 Q4 was $1.19/shr.</p>
